This channel is about Holiday displays synced to music using a module I created around the Allegro MicroSystems A80804 LED driver. The module is about the size of a thumb drive and has a 3.5mm jack on board for easily connecting to the music source. An Arduino is piggybacked onto the A80804 to convert the music input to Pulse Width Modulation (PWM) signals used to drive the A80804 individual channels of Red, Green, Blue and White LED strings. One Arduino drives five individual A80804 LED driver boards and there are no relays needed. Each module can easily drive 36 feet of basic LED strips with no need for power injection.
